<h3>How much does LG dryer repair cost in Los Angeles?</h3>
<p>Most LG dryer repairs range from $150-$350 including parts and labor. Simple fixes like thermal fuses or door latches cost around $150, while heating elements or control boards run $250-$350. We charge a $65 diagnostic fee that gets waived when you approve the repair. Complex issues like motor replacements might cost more, but our techs will give you an exact quote before starting any work.</p>
<h3>Do you offer same-day LG dryer repair service?</h3>
<p>Yes, we provide same-day service Monday through Saturday from 8am to 8pm. If you call before 4pm, we can usually get a technician out the same day. Our 85% first-visit fix rate means we solve most problems without return trips because our techs carry comprehensive parts inventories for all major LG dryer models.</p>
<h3>What are the most common LG dryer problems?</h3>
<p>The top issues we see are lint blockages in the exhaust system, blown thermal fuses from overheating, and door latch failures on DLEX series. ThinQ models often have WiFi connectivity problems or sensor malfunctions. DLGX series develop squealing noises from worn drum rollers around year three. Heating element failures are also common, especially in hard water areas.</p>
<h3>How long does an LG dryer repair typically take?</h3>
<p>Most repairs take 1-2 hours depending on the problem. Simple fixes like replacing thermal fuses or cleaning sensors might take 45 minutes, while heating element or control board replacements can take up to 2 hours. Our techs work efficiently but thoroughly test everything before leaving to ensure the repair holds up.</p>
<h3>Do you provide warranty on LG dryer repairs?</h3>
<p>Yes, we warranty all parts and labor for 90 days. We use only OEM LG parts, never aftermarket substitutes, which gives you the same reliability as factory components. If the same problem occurs within 90 days, we'll fix it at no charge. Parts defects are covered by LG's manufacturer warranty in addition to our service warranty.</p>
